@startuml Registration Check Flow

title Dynamic View - Use Case 1 Registration Check (Async External Enrichment)

autonumber
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true

actor Lawyer
participant "REST API" as API
participant "Text Check Service" as TextService
participant "Embedding Model" as Model
participant "Embedding Dataset" as Dataset
participant "Search Indexes" as Indexes
database "Trademark DB" as DB
participant "Async Job Queue" as Queue
participant "External Online Search Worker" as Worker
participant "External Online Sources" as Sources
participant "Result Delivery Service" as Delivery
participant "Similarity Engine" as Similarity
participant "Ranking Engine" as Ranking

Lawyer -> API: Submit naming + Nice classes
API -> API: Validate request
API -> API: Orchestrate workflow
API -> API: Normalize naming input
API -> TextService: Run text-only internal check with canonical input

TextService -> DB: Filter candidates by Nice classes
DB --> TextService: Candidate ids from trademark DB

par Semantic search
  TextService -> Model: Generate embedding for input naming
  Model --> TextService: Query embedding
  TextService -> Dataset: Find nearest semantic candidates
  Dataset --> TextService: Semantic shortlist
else Phonetic and text search
  TextService -> Indexes: Search by phonetic and text keys
  Indexes --> TextService: Phonetic/text shortlist
end

TextService -> TextService: Merge candidate pools

loop For each candidate
  TextService -> Similarity: Calculate detailed similarity features
  Similarity --> TextService: Semantic, phonetic, text, graphic, legal features
end

TextService -> Ranking: Build final similarity percentage and sort results
Ranking --> TextService: Top-200 internal ranked conflicts

API -> Queue: Create async external search job
Queue --> Worker: Deliver job
Worker -> Sources: Search online external sources
Sources --> Worker: External candidate set
Worker -> Ranking: Build Top-200 external ranking
Ranking --> Worker: Top-200 external ranked conflicts
Worker -> Delivery: Send delayed external result set
Delivery --> API: Top-200 external results (later)
API --> Lawyer: External enrichment update

TextService --> API: Top-200 internal result
API --> Lawyer: Top-200 internal results (fast)

note right of TextService
Responsibility: text similarity only.
No external workflow orchestration.
end note

@enduml

